, Stud. Bot. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Čech">Cech</normalizedToken>
. 9: 73, 1948
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">[Germany,] Alg. Alpen, Britzelmeyer (PRM-858488!, holotype?).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus whitish grey, endolithic. Perithecia 0.22-0.36 mm, 3/4-1-immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock. Involucrellum apical, ca. 60 mm thick, appressed to the exciple. Exciple ca. 0.24 mm in diam., wall dark. Ascospores 0-septate, 23-31 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
11-13 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
The specimen is small and only one perithecium was dissected. Our spore measurements match well with the original description (26-32 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-12(-14) mm, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Servit, M" journalOrPublisher="Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="67 - 115" refId="B48" refString="Servit, M, 1948. The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II. Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca 9: 67 - 115" title="The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II." volume="9" year="1948">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Servít">Servit</normalizedToken>
1948
</bibRefCitation>
), as well as the values given by Breuss (26-32 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
10-13 mm, according to 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.13158/heia.29.2.2016.374" author="Breuss, O" journalOrPublisher="Herzogia" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="374 - 382" refId="B8" refString="Breuss, O, 2016. Ueber einige von Miroslav Servit beschriebene Verrucaria -Arten (lichenisierte Ascomycota, Verrucariaceae). Herzogia 29 (2): 374 - 382, DOI: https://doi.org/10.13158/heia.29.2.2016.374" title="Ueber einige von Miroslav Servit beschriebene Verrucaria - Arten (lichenisierte Ascomycota, Verrucariaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.13158/heia.29.2.2016.374" volume="29" year="2016">Breuss 2016</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Servit, M" journalOrPublisher="Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="67 - 115" refId="B48" refString="Servit, M, 1948. The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II. Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca 9: 67 - 115" title="The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II." volume="9" year="1948">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Servít">Servit</normalizedToken>
(1948)
</bibRefCitation>
, the size of the exciple is 0.4 mm. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Servit, Stud. Bot. Cech. 9: 73" authorityYear="1948" class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Verrucaria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Verrucaria bavarica" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="bavarica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Verrucaria bavarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. cavernarum" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="cavernarum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. cavernarum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="V." lsidName="V. subtilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">V. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but may differ in having a larger exciple (which was not confirmed due to the very small size of the specimen) and slightly larger spores.
</paragraph>
